                    "value": "<p>15 feet. @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Aura]{Aura}</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A ghostly blue flame within the chouchin-obake draws upon the life-force of the living to sustain themself.</p>\n<p>At the start of the chouchin-obake’s turn, each creature in the aura takes [[/r 2d6 #negative]]{2d6 negative damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"26\" data-pf2-traits=\"aura,divine,necromancy,negative,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Lifewick Candle DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Fortitude</span> save). The chouchin-obake regains an amount of Hit Points equal to the amount of damage taken by the single creature that took the most damage.</p>"
